OL,6,FOn the outskirts of Pout, a rugged
OL,7,Ftown an hour by road from the
OL,8,FSenegalese capital Dakar, brewer
OL,9,FRaphael Hilarion and his small team
OL,10,Fare fighting in the trenches of West
OL,11,FAfrica's beer wars.
OL,13,FWith Senegal's beer market expected
OL,14,Fto be worth #50m a year by 2025,
OL,15,FHilarion is confident his Kalao craft
OL,16,Fbeers ` among them stouts, IPAs and
OL,17,Fpilsners ` can chip away at the
OL,18,Fdominance of the country's two
OL,19,Fflagship lager producers, Flag and
OL,20,FGazelle, and perhaps even push into
OL,21,Fbeer-mad Nigeria.
OL,3,CHow fonio, a forgotten superfood,
OL,4,Cbecame a weapon in Africa's beer wars
